tspan.tspan: ClockIOT
Internet
Of
Clocks
Quick Start :
First turn On (one time WiFi setup)
By default, ClockIOT expects to be in range of a WiFi hotspot.
When it boots for the first time, it will create a temporary WiFi
hotspot called "KLOK" & display "KLOK" using letters on the
faceplate as pixels.
Using a computer or phone, find & join "KLOK" network.
This will bring you to the welcome screen (or enter
192.168.4.1 in a browser).
Enter your WiFi credentials.
ClockIOT will store them and reset.
Once on the internet, ClockIOT will look up the UTC (Zulu)
time using NTP, and your timezone from wyolum.com
courtesy of ipapi.co. And you are all set!!

to control ClockIOT.
